<br>
Good luck!<br>
<br>
Tkiam <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 67<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/9/02 2:48:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1072.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Having some trouble with a corpse</span><hr size=1> Its possible. If you were in motion when you went LD you tend to stay in motion.<br>
<br>
Did you try the /corpse command? This will do two things.<br>
<br>
First, it will tell you if you have a corpse in the zone. You will get the message &quot;Your corpse is to far away to summon it&quot; or you will get the message &quot;You do not have any corpses in this zone&quot;.<br>
<br>
The second thing it does is &quot;summon&quot; your corpse to you. You do need to be close to it for this to work though. Hopefully a necro or neutral bard will read this post and be able to help you. Barring that, if you can retrace your steps and head along the same path you were going when you went LD you should be able to follow the same path (into the water perhaps) until you see your corpse. At level 15, anything in the water that would have engaged you would have mmost likely defeated you. So your character shouldnt have &quot;chased&quot; them around while LD.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.<br>
 <p>Kzan Verto<BR>
Giver of "da juice" (tm)
